## Linux x86_64 (Primary)

The primary development and deployment platform.

### Rust
- Builds out of the box with `cargo build`
- GUI requires: libxkbcommon, libGL, wayland, X11 libs, Vulkan loader, fontconfig, freetype
- On NixOS, `nix develop` provides everything
- On Debian/Ubuntu: `sudo apt install libxkbcommon-dev libgl-dev libwayland-dev libx11-dev libxcursor-dev libxi-dev libxrandr-dev libvulkan-dev libfontconfig-dev libfreetype-dev`

### Python
- Full support — OR-Tools, CustomTkinter, PyInstaller
- Tk required for GUI: `sudo apt install python3-tk`
- CI tests run on Ubuntu with `xvfb` for headless GUI testing

## Linux ARM64 (aarch64-linux)

Supported for Raspberry Pi, ARM servers, and cloud instances.

### Rust
- CLI works well via cross-rs
- GUI builds but requires ARM-compatible GPU drivers for rendering
- egui falls back to software rendering if no GPU is available

### Python
- OR-Tools has ARM64 wheels for Linux
- CustomTkinter works if Tk is available
- PyInstaller produces ARM64 binaries natively

## macOS Intel (x86_64-darwin)

### Rust
- Requires Xcode command-line tools
- Uses AppKit, Metal, CoreGraphics, CoreText frameworks for GUI
- Can only build macOS targets on macOS (Apple SDK requirement)
- `cargo build --release` works out of the box

### Python
- Full support — all dependencies have macOS wheels
- GUI uses CustomTkinter (Tk is bundled with macOS Python)
- PyInstaller produces `.app` bundles

## macOS Apple Silicon (aarch64-darwin)

### Rust
- Same as Intel macOS but uses native ARM instructions
- Metal rendering is particularly fast on Apple Silicon
- Universal binaries possible with `lipo` (combine x86_64 + aarch64)

### Python
- Full support via native ARM Python from python.org or Homebrew
- OR-Tools provides ARM64 macOS wheels
- Rosetta 2 can run x86_64 builds if needed

## Windows

### Rust
- Native build requires MSVC toolchain (Visual Studio Build Tools)
- Cross-compilation from Linux uses `x86_64-pc-windows-gnu` target
- CLI works fully cross-compiled
- GUI cross-compilation is limited (needs MinGW windowing libraries)
- Recommended: build natively on Windows for GUI

### Python
- Full support — CI tests run on Windows 11
- CustomTkinter works natively (Tk bundled with Python)
- PyInstaller produces `.exe` files
- OR-Tools provides Windows wheels

## Android

### Python only
- Built with Kivy + buildozer
- OR-Tools unavailable — uses nearest-neighbor solver
- Requires Android SDK/NDK (buildozer downloads automatically)
- Tested via CI with spec validation (full APK build requires self-hosted runner)

### Rust
- Not currently targeted for Android
- theoretically possible via cargo-ndk for CLI use via Termux
